==English==
===Etymology===
From the [[w:French_language|French]] ''[[garçon]]'' (1788)

===Noun===
'''garçon'''
# A [[waiter]] (especially at a French [[restaurant]]).

===Alternate spellings===
*[[garcon]]

===References===
''Merriam-Webster's Collegiate Dictionary: Tenth Edition'' (1997)

==French==

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /ɡaʁ.sɔ̃/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /gaR.sO~/

===Etymology===
Of Germanic origin, akin to the [[w:Old_High_German_language|OHG]] ''[[hrechjo]]'', ''[[fugitive]].''

===Noun===
'''garçon''' ''m'', '''[[garçons]]''' ''pl''
# A [[boy]]
#:''Il a deux garçons et une fille''
#::''He has two boys and a girl.''
# [[waiter]]
#:''Eh, garçon, viens ici, je veux payer.''
#::''Oi, waiter, come here, I want to pay.''

